## F. Quality Gates

**All gates must pass** before returning the test plan. Fix and re-verify — never output a failing plan.

| # | Gate | Applies to |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | **Budget: 10-12 test cases total.** Consolidate before outputting if over 12. | Both |
| 2 | ADR fully decomposed; missing sections noted | ADR only |
| 3 | Every goal and risk maps to at least one REQ | ADR only |
| 4 | PR diff analyzed, all changed files categorized | PR only |
| 5 | Every significant code change maps to a requirement with confidence level | PR only |
| 6 | Assumptions about design intent are explicit | PR only |
| 7 | Gaps needing ADR confirmation are documented | PR only |
| 8 | E2E minimum: at least one positive-path and one negative-path test | Both |
| 9 | NEG minimum: at least 2 destructive tests (config resilience + component restart) | Both |
| 10 | MQE minimum: at least one acceptance or exploratory test | Both |
| 11 | Traceability complete: every REQ has a test or "NOT COVERED" justification | Both |
| 12 | Traceability source: every test cites ADR section or Jira AC — not PRs/commits | ADR only |
| 13 | No tier duplication: same observable not tested in both E2E and NFT | Both |
| 14 | No vague steps: every step has concrete action + observable outcome | Both |
| 15 | Cleanup specified for every test that creates resources | Both |
| 16 | Priority assigned (Critical / High / Medium) to every test | Both |
| 17 | Scope respected: no tests for Non-Goals unless regression guard | Both |
| 18 | No redundancy: two tests covering the same observable must be merged | Both |

